content.text:
The issue was that the pre-publish screen (modal) was showing a "Categories" selection option even for Pages, which do not support categories. Additionally, there was unused code suggesting an intention to handle this but it was not correctly implemented.

I modified `WordPress/src/main/java/org/wordpress/android/ui/posts/prepublishing/home/PrepublishingHomeViewModel.kt` to:
1.  Wrap the logic for adding the Categories item to the UI state in a check for `!editPostRepository.isPage`. This ensures categories are only shown for Posts, not Pages.
2.  Clean up dead and incorrect code in `setupHomeUiState` and `showNotSetPost` that was creating unused `UiString` objects or trying to handle categories incorrectly.

These changes prevent the "Categories" option from appearing when publishing a Page, resolving the reported issue.

```kotlin
// In setupHomeUiState method of PrepublishingHomeViewModel.kt

// Before:
/*
            if (!editPostRepository.isPage) {
                showNotSetPost(editPostRepository, site)
            } else {
                UiStringRes(R.string.prepublishing_nudges_home_categories_not_set)
            }

            val categoriesString = getCategoriesUseCase.getPostCategoriesString(
                editPostRepository,
                site
            )

            add(HomeUiState(
                navigationAction = PrepublishingScreenNavigation.Categories,
                ...
            ))
*/

// After:
            if (!editPostRepository.isPage) {
                showNotSetPost(editPostRepository, site)

                val categoriesString = getCategoriesUseCase.getPostCategoriesString(
                    editPostRepository,
                    site
                )

                add(HomeUiState(
                    navigationAction = PrepublishingScreenNavigation.Categories,
                    ...
                ))
            }
```

I also removed dead code from `showNotSetPost`.

I verified the code changes with `read_lints` and found no errors.

